Change the date to 30 days from existing 15 days for UWD/EDB status change to Non-Renew
Description

Requirements

R1) Status in EBD for renewals which are not issued in Phoenix and after 30 days past their expiry date should be changed to non-renew. Currently the functionality is happening, but the status is changing after 15 days past the policy expiry date. 

R2) Change in number of days should be applicable for commercial auto and middle market. 

Acceptance Criteria 1:

As a 

product user

when 

the current date is past 30 days after the policy expiry date (Renewal effective date), and the renewal transaction is not yet issued in Phoenix

then I want

EDB to update the status as non-renew in EDB/UWD.

Acceptance Criteria 2:

As a 

product user

when 

the current date is past 30 days after the policy expiry date (Renewal effective date), and the renewal transaction is issued in Phoenix

then I want

EDB to update the status as per Phoenix and it should not be non-renew. 

 

Acceptance Criteria 3:

As a 

product user

when 

the current date is past 15 days after the policy expiry date (Renewal effective date), and the renewal transaction is not yet issued in Phoenix

then I want

EDB to update the status as per Phoenix and it should not be non-renew. 